</b></p>
<p>119.48 Continue efforts to promote women&#8217;s participation in public decision 
</p>
<p><b>taking (Honduras); 
</b></p>
<p>119.49 <b>Continue to address the root causes of unemployment, especially 
</b></p>
<p><b>among young people, by adopting the necessary long-term policies and 
</b></p>
<p><b>strategies (Trinidad and Tobago);  
</b></p>
<p>119.50 <b>Continue strengthening its sound social plans and programs in favour 
</b></p>
<p><b>of its people </b>&#8212;<b> with a particular emphasis in the areas of education, food and 
</b></p>
<p><b>health </b>&#8212;<b> for which it is very important to have the support of the community 
</b></p>
<p><b>of nations, through the cooperation that the country might require (Bolivarian 
</b></p>
<p><b>Republic of Venezuela); 
</b></p>
<p>119.51 <b>Augment their efforts to reduce poverty and to provide enhanced 
</b></p>
